<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-07-1224 </DOCNO><TEXT>The concentrations of thyrotropin, thyroglobulin, calcitonin and carcinoembryonicantigen were raised in the blood of thyroid cancer patients. The occurrenceof relapses of regional and distant metastases was accompanied by a sharpincrease in the levels of thyrotropin, thyroglobulin and carcinoembryonicantigen permitting the recommendation of these tests for the diagnosisof distant metastases in the absence of local spread of a process. Simultaneousdetermination of the levels of thyroglobulins and carcinoembryonic antigenwas the most informative for defining metastatic involvement of the osseoussystem.</TEXT></DOC>